                <td bgcolor="#000000" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2">Malbegotten</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#000000" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/09/2003&nbsp;: 3:13:18 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> You don't need KEI here if you have a lifetap memmed, like Deflux or Drain Soul.  I keep myself liched most of the time, and use BoD to keep my hitpoints from dropping while pacting my pet, but need lifetaps to keep alive while liching.  The lifetap also works great to take out a low health guard if you get an add.</span></font></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2">Xabbel Mal`Farious</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/09/2003&nbsp;: 2:26:28 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> This is a repsonse on how to pull the front bridge guards single.  What seems to work for me is getting on the right side of the tunnel into Felwith proper and getting back in the corner.  I try to cast splurt from max casting range and usually that will get one as long as you do not move until they are far enough away from the second guard to aggro. For some reason, every time I cast then immediately ran, they both came.  May be because of the funky pathing they have.  I have not tried since the patch, but I was able to single pull at 51 pre-patch.<br /><br />On a different note, I have recently started pulling with nullify magic.  Gets rid of daring and whatever else it is they cast when they pop.  I usally pull with it, cast it again, then splurt, then pact pet, then cast ignite, then BoD, then sit down.  I reapply pact as needed.  If I get a dual wielder, I may cast Torbas as well to get them down faster.<br /><br />My spell lineup is Bond of Death, Splurt, Nullify Magic, Ignite Blood, Augment Death, Torbas, Pact of Shadow.  I forget the last one.  I am currently 52.<br /><br />Welcome to your doom!</span></font></td>
