              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2">Xabbel Mal`Farious</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/03/2003&nbsp;: 09:27:37 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> I have just started here at 51, but I like the front.  If you are facing the bridge in the tunnel, hug right wall and move back as far as possible then cast splurt or nullify/annul magic on the guard on the RIGHT.  Don't run just yet. The key here is to wait for the guard to run past the the guard on the left and get out of the other guards aggro range.  If you cast then run, you will pull both.  When he gets close, run around the corner to where your pet is set up and sic pet on guard.<br /><br />I cast splurt if I have not pulled with it, then ignite blood.  I have had very few resists with ignite.  I usually sit then pact my pet and cast cast BoD, sit again.  They usually go down fairly easy, but not without a fight.  I keep Torbas Poison blast memmed in case I get an add and need to put the 1st one down fast.  It get resisted, but only about 33% of the time.  It has instant recast so if it is resisted try again.  I occasionly get run out of the zone if I get one of the tougher guards (hit for 104) or two dual weilders.  In general though, great money and xp.  KEI is a must here as stated before.<br /><br />Welcome to your doom!</span></font></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#000000" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2">Malbegotten</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#000000" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/01/2003&nbsp;: 10:30:00 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> My tips:<br /><br />I like the Faydark side of this zone... just can't seem to get the spawn timing right on the back side and always end up with adds.<br /><br />I use the lvl 49 pet instead of 53 pet here because the 49 pet has more hitpoints and he'll be tanking.<br /><br />I pull with splurt, then pact my pet.  Then I Bond of Death the guard.  Med up, keep pet pacted... I use my highest Lifetap to get extra health for myself and help my pet with dual wielding guards.  I never fear or darkness these guys... not necessary and not smart with all the potential for adds.<br /><br />Malbegotten Deadrot<br />Heretic of the 53rd Level<br />The Seventh Hammer</span></font></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2">Izlana</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;03/31/2003&nbsp;: 1:48:48 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Since I just started hunting these guards I'll share my experience. :)<br /><br />There are 2 places to set up camp...up front near the zone to GF or right next to Elytan Rantas in the back near the water.<br /><br />Some general rules:<br /><br />1.  Don't bother with any poison or disease DoTs...they seem to get resisted more than half the time. I did not try hitting them with Scent of Terris before applying poison or disease DoT...I wanted to save mana.<br /><br />2.  Pull with Splurt...this DoT is never resisted. At level 52 I can single pull either of the 2 guards at the front of the bridge (if camping near GF)...just make sure to pull at maximum range.<br /><br />3.  If you're camping near GF there's a grassy area in front of first 2 bridge guards where guards Legver and Mystan spawn. Every time I tried to pull guards at this spawn point I agroed both front bridge guards...so clear the bridge guards first and wait for roamers to come back.<br /><br />4.  You can sit safely near GF zone once you've cleared Guard Legver...he is the only guard that roams all the way to GF zone line...all other roamers stop at grassy area in front of bridge.<br /><br />5.  Don't bother snaring guards because it's resisted at least half the time and they turn to run at much lower % HP because they sit and try to heal themselves. Chances are if they turn to run your DoTs and pet will kill them before they've made it 3 steps.<br /><br />6.  The exception to #5 is this: if you pull a guard that's dual wielding (holding 2 swords) they take pet down alot faster so I cast darkness for the extra damage.<br /><br />7.  If you're hunting near the back you only need to get close to bank to aggro Guard Evital. approach bank close to wall not building and back in until you get aggro message. Doing it this way I've never aggroed the banker.<br /><br />8.  You will need to Pact your pet at least once...most likely twice if the guard is dark blue or higher...so throw BoD on guard as well as Splurt.<br /><br />9.  Fearing guards...don't bother.  It usually wears off in 3 seconds.<br /><br />10.  The exception to #9. If your pet is down to 20% health sometimes I'll fear the guard it's fighting and then /pet back off...this buys me a tick or 2 of Pact to heal pet before fear breaks and guard comes running back. This is not recommended if you are near other guards.<br /><br />11.  Adds. I find zoning is much easier if I accidentally pull 2 at once...ST gets resisted ALOT and root breaks as quick as Fear does.<br /><br />12.  Bring weight reducing bags to hold the swords these guys drop...unless you want to run and sell every 20 minutes. I get by with a Rallic pack, Sharlok pack and Herbilist Pack...that usually lasts me an hour. If I get too filled up I find a newbie in the zone and have him sell for me. <br /></span></font></td>
              </tr>
